Class hier_scaffolds_utils

  • Object
    • hier_scaffolds_utils

  • public class hier_scaffolds_utils
extends Object
    Contains static functions used in hierarchical scaffold analysis. These public API functions for use in applications.
    Author:
    Jeremy J Yang
    See Also:
    ScaffoldTree, Scaffold, Linker, Sidechain, hier_scaffolds

      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static boolean CheckExistsDB(String dbhost, int dbport, String dbname, String dbschema, String dbusr, String dbpw, String dbtableprefix)
      Minimal sanity check whether DB exists ("scaffold" and "scaf2scaf" tables) to support ScaffoldDB object.
      static float commonScaffoldTanimoto(ScaffoldTree scaftreeA, ScaffoldTree scaftreeB)
      Returns similarity metric designed to reflect the significance of the maximum common scaffold between two molecules. Given by the formula:
        sim = nc / (na + nb - nc)
      where
        nc = # atoms in common scaffold
        na = # atoms in max scaffold, mol A
        nb = # atoms in max scaffold, mol B
      This is an experimental functionality. Intended for use in combination with a standard whole-molecule similarity metric.
      static float commonScaffoldTanimoto(ScaffoldTree scaftreeA, ScaffoldTree scaftreeB, Scaffold mcScaf)
      Returns similarity metric designed to reflect the significance of the maximum common scaffold between two molecules. Given by the formula:
        sim = nc / (na + nb - nc)
      where
        nc = # atoms in common scaffold
        na = # atoms in max scaffold, mol A
        nb = # atoms in max scaffold, mol B
      This is an experimental functionality. Intended for use in combination with a standard whole-molecule similarity metric. Use this faster method if mcScaf is already calculated (with maxCommonScaffold()).
